message: “I never heard much about human trafficking prior to being first lady,” Edwards said. “It’s one of those issues where you think, ‘Oh, that doesn’t happen in my community.’ But it does. In fact, Louisiana has one of the highest trafficked areas.”

data.description: Louisiana first lady Donna Edwards met with local officials today at the Terrebonne Children’s Advocacy Center to discuss ways to combat
data.title: Louisiana's first lady visits Houma to dicuss human trafficking
